request.description:
# Place Order

Creates a new order for the authenticated user.

- Method: `POST`

- URL: `http://{{base-url}}/orders`

- Auth: Bearer token using `{{auth-token}}` (set in the active environment)

- Content-Type: `application/json`


### Request body

Send a JSON object with an array of items. Each item contains a product_id and quantity.

``` json
{
  "items": [
    { "product_id": 1, "quantity": 2 },
    { "product_id": 2, "quantity": 4 }
  ]
}

 ```

Schema (guide):

``` json
{
  "type": "object",
  "properties": {
    "items": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "properties": {
          "product_id": { "type": "integer", "enum": [1,2,8,9] },
          "quantity": { "type": "integer", "enum": [2,4,5,6] }
        },
        "required": ["product_id", "quantity"]
      }
    }
  },
  "required": ["items"]
}

 ```

### Successful response

On success, returns 201 Created with the new order details.

``` json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": {
    "order_id": 3,
    "user_id": 1,
    "total": 570,
    "total_discount": 30,
    "created_at": "2026-01-03T02:51:42.760575467Z",
    "items": [
      { "product_id": 1, "quantity": 2, "unit_price": 100 },
      { "product_id": 2, "quantity": 4, "unit_price": 100 }
    ]
  }
}

 ```

### Notes

- Uses `{{base-url}}` and requires `{{auth-token}}` in the environment.

- Ensure `Content-Type: application/json` header is present.
